  "primaryContentSections": [
    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "In this sample code project, you’ll convert a 3-channel 8-bit ARGB image to a 1-channel grayscale image by using a matrix of coefficients that define the color conversion."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "vImage provides matrix multiplication operations that offer functionality analogous to the dot product (that is, returning the sum of the products of the corresponding elements in two vectors). "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/accelerate/1546979-vimagematrixmultiply_argb8888top"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " and "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/accelerate/1546678-vimagematrixmultiply_argbfffftop"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " multiply each channel of an interleaved image with a value in a matrix and return the sum of the multiplications to a planar image."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "The following shows how "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "vImageMatrixMultiply_ARGB8888ToPlanar8"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " calculates the result for each pixel:"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "codeListing",
          "code": [
            "let p = (sourcePixels[index].a + preBias.a) * matrix.a +",
            "        (sourcePixels[index].r + preBias.r) * matrix.r +",
            "        (sourcePixels[index].g + preBias.g) * matrix.g +",
            "        (sourcePixels[index].b + preBias.b) * matrix.b",
            "",
            "let destinationPixels[index] = (p + postBias) / divisor"
          ],
          "syntax": "swift",
          "metadata": {
            "anchor": "3283257",
            "title": "Listing 1"
          }
        },
        {
          "level": 3,
          "type": "heading",
          "text": "Define the Coefficient Values",
          "anchor": "3283272"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Luma coefficients model an eye’s response to red, green, and blue light. The following formula shows the Rec. 709 luma coefficients for the color-to-grayscale conversion, and it calculates luminance. In the formula, "
            },
            {
              "type": "emphasis",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": "Y"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " represents the luminance of the red, green, and blue values:"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "image",
              "identifier": "media-3283259",
              "metadata": {
                "anchor": "3283259",
                "title": "Figure 1"
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "The following shows how you declare the luma coefficients:"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "codeListing",
          "code": [
            "let redCoefficient: Float = 0.2126",
            "let greenCoefficient: Float = 0.7152",
            "let blueCoefficient: Float = 0.0722"
          ],
          "syntax": "swift",
          "metadata": {
            "anchor": "3283260",
            "title": "Listing 2"
          }
        },
        {
          "level": 3,
          "type": "heading",
          "text": "Define the Coefficients Matrix",
          "anchor": "3283273"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "vImageMatrixMultiply_ARGB8888ToPlanar8"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " accepts integer values for the matrix; multiply each fractional coefficient in the matrix by "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "divisor"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ":"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "codeListing",
          "code": [
            "let divisor: Int32 = 0x1000",
            "let fDivisor = Float(divisor)",
            "",
            "var coefficientsMatrix = [",
            "    Int16(redCoefficient * fDivisor),",
            "    Int16(greenCoefficient * fDivisor),",
            "    Int16(blueCoefficient * fDivisor)",
            "]"
          ],
          "syntax": "swift",
          "metadata": {
            "anchor": "3283262",
            "title": "Listing 3"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "The matrix multiply function requires an "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/swift/int32"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "divisor"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ", but the coefficients are "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/swift/float"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " values. To simplify the matrix initialization, declare and use "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "fDivisor"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " to multiply each coefficients by the divisor."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "level": 3,
          "type": "heading",
          "text": "Perform the Matrix Multiply",
          "anchor": "3283274"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "The color-to-grayscale calculation is the sum of the products of each color value and its corresponding coefficient, so define pre- and post-bias as zero. Call "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "vImageMatrixMultiply_ARGB8888ToPlanar8"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " to perform the matrix multiplication:"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "codeListing",
          "code": [
            "let preBias: [Int16] = [0, 0, 0, 0]",
            "let postBias: Int32 = 0",
            "",
            "vImageMatrixMultiply_ARGB8888ToPlanar8(&sourceBuffer,",
            "                                       &destinationBuffer,",
            "                                       &coefficientsMatrix,",
            "                                       divisor,",
            "                                       preBias,",
            "                                       postBias,",
            "                                       vImage_Flags(kvImageNoFlags))"
          ],
          "syntax": "swift",
          "metadata": {
            "anchor": "3283264",
            "title": "Listing 4"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "On return, the "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "destinationBuffer"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " contains a grayscale representation of your original image."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "level": 3,
          "type": "heading",
          "text": "Create a Grayscale Core Graphics Image",
          "anchor": "3283275"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Finally, you can create a 1-channel grayscale "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/coregraphics/cgimageref"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " instance from the destination buffer. The image format contains 8 bits per component and 8 bits per pixel. A single channel format has the same number of bits per pixel as bits per component."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "codeListing",
          "code": [
            "guard let monoFormat = vImage_CGImageFormat(",
            "    bitsPerComponent: 8,",
            "    bitsPerPixel: 8,",
            "    colorSpace: CGColorSpaceCreateDeviceGray(),",
            "    bitmapInfo: CGBitmapInfo(rawValue: CGImageAlphaInfo.none.rawValue),",
            "    renderingIntent: .defaultIntent) else {",
            "        return",
            "}"
          ],
          "syntax": "swift",
          "metadata": {
            "anchor": "3283267",
            "title": "Listing 5"
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "To create the image, pass the destination buffer and grayscale format to "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/accelerate/vimage_buffer/3241529-createcgimage"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ":"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
